          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "transcribing",
          "value": "The enlarged ayin at the end of Shma (Hear) and the enlarged dalet at the end of \nechad (one) combine to spell eid (witness). We recite the Shma to bear witness to the Oneness of God.\nBaruch shem kvod... Blessed is God's glorious... M. Yoma 3:8, inspired by Nehemiah 9:5",
